BARBERTON – A retired correctional officer, Banks Nkosi, was left unharmed after his Toyota Avanza collided with a BMW sedan. The accident happened along General Street on Wednesday afternoon. Nkosi’s Avanza was coming from the Jock of the Bushveld Shopping Centre to join General Street, while the BMW was driving towards town when the two cars collided.  Traffic was slightly disrupted. City of Mbombela Local Municipality and SAPS officers arrived on the scene to control the traffic. Both drivers were unharmed. Jabu Ndubane, police spokesman, said an accident report was recorded. Also Read: Massive dagga plantation discovered in the Lowveld